HEADWORD: Imposthumation
<hw>Im*post`hu*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of forming an abscess; state of being inflamed;
suppuration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An abscess; an imposthume.</def>
<rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imposthume</ent>⟦br⟧
